sentences: Marion Zarzeczna (November 11, 1930 – June 1, 2020) was an American concert pianist and educator.
She received her Bachelor of Music degree in 1954 from the Curtis Institute of Music, where she studied with Mieczysław Horszowski.
She joined the faculty of The Curtis Institute of Music in 1962.
She was on the faculty of Westminster Choir College beginning in 1972 as well as a member of the Greater Trenton Symphony Orchestra
Marion Zarzeczna died on June 1, 2020, aged 89, in her native Trenton, New Jersey.
